abstract: Rep. Elissa Slotkin, a freshman Democrat who flipped a Republican seat in battleground Michigan, said Monday she will vote to impeach President Donald Trump, defending her position during a rowdy town hall.
snippet: Rep. Elissa Slotkin, a freshman Democrat who flipped a Republican seat in battleground Michigan, said Monday she will vote to impeach President Donald Trump, defending her position during a rowdy town hall.
lead_paragraph: ROCHESTER, Mich. — Rep. Elissa Slotkin, a freshman Democrat who flipped a Republican seat in battleground Michigan, said Monday she will vote to impeach President Donald Trump, defending her position during a rowdy town hall.
headline_main: Michigan Rep. Slotkin Says She Will Vote to Impeach Trump
headline_print_headline: Michigan Rep. Slotkin Says She Will Vote to Impeach Trump

abstract: New lawmakers may have realized a lifetime ambition. But with a huge Conservative majority, individual members will have little influence.
snippet: New lawmakers may have realized a lifetime ambition. But with a huge Conservative majority, individual members will have little influence.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — There was no hiding the excitement on Monday as new members of Britain’s Parliament descended on the Palace of Westminster for day one of their new lives, most propelled there by the landslide victory of Boris Johnson’s Conservative Party.

abstract: Former Central African President Francois Bozize, who was ousted nearly seven years ago by a coalition of rebel groups, has returned from exile, his political party announced Monday.
snippet: Former Central African President Francois Bozize, who was ousted nearly seven years ago by a coalition of rebel groups, has returned from exile, his political party announced Monday.
lead_paragraph: BANGUI, Central African Republic — Former Central African President Francois Bozize, who was ousted nearly seven years ago by a coalition of rebel groups, has returned from exile, his political party announced Monday.
headline_main: Central African Republic Ex-Leader Bozize Returns From Exile
headline_print_headline: Central African Republic Ex-Leader Bozize Returns From Exile

abstract: An associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani on Monday urged a judge to let him stay free on bail while he awaits trial, denying prosecutors' accusations that he lied about receiving a $1 million payment from Russia shortly before he was arrested.
snippet: An associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani on Monday urged a judge to let him stay free on bail while he awaits trial, denying prosecutors' accusations that he lied about receiving a $1 million payment from Russia ...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — An associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani on Monday urged a judge to let him stay free on bail while he awaits trial, denying prosecutors' accusations that he lied about receiving a $1 million payment from Russia shortly before he was arrested.
headline_main: Giuliani Associate Denies Hiding Russian Payment, Asks to Stay Free on Bail
headline_print_headline: Giuliani Associate Denies Hiding Russian Payment, Asks to Stay Free on Bail

abstract: Years of drought, erratic weather and other stresses are taking their toll on the peppers that are central to the state’s economy and identity.
snippet: Years of drought, erratic weather and other stresses are taking their toll on the peppers that are central to the state’s economy and identity.
lead_paragraph: HATCH, N.M. — In all her eight decades of farming in southeastern New Mexico, June Rutherford has never seen a chile season this bad.

abstract: He was a staunch defender of the president amid the administration’s Watergate crisis and later served as Gerald Ford’s trade representative.
snippet: He was a staunch defender of the president amid the administration’s Watergate crisis and later served as Gerald Ford’s trade representative.
lead_paragraph: Frederick B. Dent, a South Carolina textile manufacturer who in the mid-1970s was President Richard M. Nixon’s secretary of commerce and President Gerald R. Ford’s special representative for United States trade negotiations, died on Dec. 10 in Spartanburg, S.C. He was 97.

abstract: Representative Elissa Slotkin, a moderate Democrat from Michigan, announced Monday that she would vote to impeach President Trump — and quickly faced the consequences.
snippet: Representative Elissa Slotkin, a moderate Democrat from Michigan, announced Monday that she would vote to impeach President Trump — and quickly faced the consequences.
lead_paragraph: HOLLY, Mich. — Impeaching President Trump, Representative Elissa Slotkin said, “was pretty much the last thing I wanted to be working on in my first term as a congressperson.”

abstract: Britain's financial sector can withstand large shocks and disruptions, whether from a disorderly Brexit or a deterioration in global trade wars, the Bank of England said Monday.

abstract: Carly Fiorina, a 2016 GOP presidential candidate, says “it is vital” that President Donald Trump be impeached, but she did not go so far as to say he should be removed from office.
snippet: Carly Fiorina, a 2016 GOP presidential candidate, says “it is vital” that President Donald Trump be impeached, but she did not go so far as to say he should be removed from office.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Carly Fiorina, a 2016 GOP presidential candidate, says “it is vital” that President Donald Trump be impeached, but she did not go so far as to say he should be removed from office.
headline_main: 2016 GOP Candidate Fiorina Calls Trump's Impeachment 'Vital'
